  "instructions": [
    "preheat the grill to medium-high heat.",
    "season the pork knuckle with salt, black pepper, paprika, cumin, coriander, and minced garlic.",
    "in a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, and sliced ginger.",
    "brush the mixture evenly over the pork knuckle, making sure to coat all surfaces.",
    "place the pork knuckle on the grill and cook for 5 minutes per side, or until it reaches an internal temperature of 160f.",
    "let the pork knuckle rest for 5 minutes before slicing it into thin pieces, or 'sashimi-cut'.",
    "serve with a side of roasted vegetables, garnished with chopped fresh parsley."
